  number    = "4\_suppl",
  pages     = "409--409",
  abstract  = "409 Background: MEK (mitogen-activated protein kinase kinase) is
               activated through mutated KRAS in > 90\% of PDAC. Focal adhesion
               kinase (FAK) integrates signals from integrins and growth factor
               receptors. MEK and FAK are frequently co-activated in PDAC
