               learning from raw data and led to numerous high-profile success
               stories3-5, gradient-boosted decision trees6-9 have dominated
               tabular data for the past 20 years. Here we present the Tabular
               Prior-data Fitted Network (TabPFN), a tabular foundation model
               that outperforms all previous methods on datasets with up to
               10,000 samples by a wide margin, using substantially less
               training time. In 2.8 s, TabPFN outperforms an ensemble of the
               strongest baselines tuned for 4 h in a classification setting. As
               a generative transformer-based foundation model, this model also
               allows fine-tuning, data generation, density estimation and
               learning reusable embeddings. TabPFN is a learning algorithm that
               is itself learned across millions of synthetic datasets,
