  volume    =  19,
  number    =  2,
  pages     = "e1010888",
  abstract  = "Protein kinases play a vital role in a wide range of cellular
               processes, and compounds that inhibit kinase activity emerging as
               a primary focus for targeted therapy development, especially in
               cancer. Consequently, efforts to characterize the behavior of
               kinases in response to inhibitor treatment, as well as downstream
