              strongest predictors of mortality, while CRRT timing showed
              relatively lower impact on outcome prediction. Conclusion: While
              later initiation of CRRT in S-AKI patients was associated with
              improved survival, this benefit comes with increased healthcare
              resource utilization. The clinical parameters, rather than CRRT
              timing, are the primary determinants of patient outcomes,
              suggesting the need for a more personalized approach to CRRT
              initiation based on overall illness severity.",
