  number   =  9,
  pages    = "2228--2239",
  abstract = "BACKGROUND: Sepiapterin reductase (SPR) is an important regulator
              of the biosynthesis of tetrahydrobiopterin (BH4), which has been
              shown to be a promoter of different kinds of tumors. This study
              aims to investigate the role of SPR in breast cancer and to
